SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 892
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor the United States men's hockey team
on winning the gold medal at the 2026 Olympic
Games on an overtime goal by Jack Hughes.
WHEREAS, the United States men's hockey team has brought great pride and joy to
Americans from all walks of life by emerging victorious from the 2026 Olympic Games as gold
medalists and world champions; and
WHEREAS, Team USA defeated archrival Canada in overtime in the final match to claim
our nation's third gold medal in men's hockey, exactly forty-six years after 1980's "Miracle on
Ice" by America's last men's gold-medal team in the sport; and
WHEREAS, the 2026 Milan Cortina Games mark the first time that the U.S. has won
gold in men's hockey at an Olympics in which NHL players were competing; and
WHEREAS, the U.S. squad was unbeaten heading into the gold medal tilt, having
outscored its opponents 24-8 in winning five consecutive games; and
WHEREAS, the U.S. men's hockey team steamrolled Latvia, Denmark, and Germany in
the preliminary matches of the tournament to advance to the first knockout round; and
WHEREAS, in their quarterfinal game, the Stars and Stripes faced off against an
excellent Sweden squad and took an early lead on a goal by Dylan Larkin; and
WHEREAS, after Sweden tied the game late in the third period, Quinn Hughes delivered
the golden goal at 3:27 of overtime to propel the U.S. team to victory; he also led the U.S. in
total points for the Games with eight and was named the tournament's Best Defender; and
WHEREAS, Team USA then routed Slovakia 6-2 in the semifinals to earn a berth in the
gold medal match, in which Matt Boldy scored a beautiful goal early in the first period to give the
Americans the lead; however, the Canadians countered with an equalizer late in the second
period; and
SJR0892
