- 1 -

WHEREAS, after a scoreless third period, the gold medal match entered sudden-
decision overtime; just like Superman, Team USA's Jack Hughes then saved the day, finding
the back of the net at 1:41 to earn his team the 2-1 victory, the Olympic gold medal, and the title
of world champions; and
WHEREAS, to add to this already storybook ending: Jack Hughes was the victim of a
high-sticking double-minor penalty by Canada late in regulation; bleeding from the mouth and
missing several teeth, he displayed his inner fortitude by returning to the ice and scoring the
golden goal in overtime; and
WHEREAS, even though he is now recognized as the ultimate hero of the U.S. team,
Jack Hughes would be the first to acknowledge that Connor Hellebuyck, who was named the
tournament's Best Goaltender, was the deciding factor in the final match, as he put on a
highlight-reel performance in goal that has already become legendary in hockey history; and
WHEREAS, the brotherhood of Team USA was on full display after their historic victory;
the U.S. players celebrated on the ice with their late teammate Johnny Gaudreau's jersey, as
his family looked on from the crowd in Milan; and
WHEREAS, in fact, Johnny Gaudreau's jersey was hung in the American locker room
throughout the tournament as a tribute to this outstanding hockey player and human being, who
tragically lost his life in 2024 at the age of thirty-one; and
WHEREAS, in addition to the aforementioned athletes, each of the other U.S. men's
hockey players contributed significantly to the success of the team, including Jeremy Swayman,
Jake Oettinger, Jack Eichel, alternate captain Charlie McAvoy, captain Auston Matthews,
alternate captain Matthew Tkachuk, Brock Nelson, Brady Tkachuk, Zach Werenski, J.T. Miller,
Kyle Connor, Jackson LaCombe, Noah Hanifin, Tage Thompson, Jaccob Slavin, Jake
Sanderson, Jake Guentzel, Brock Faber, Vincent Trocheck, and Clayton Keller; and
- 2 - 014465

WHEREAS, Team USA enjoyed outstanding leadership in the front office and on the
bench, in the persons of head coach Mike Sullivan and general manager Bill Guerin; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Team USA for winning
the Olympic gold medal in men's hockey while representing their country with patriotism and
passion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the players, coaches,
and staff members of the United States men's hockey team on winning the gold medal at the
2026 Olympic Games, praising their performance on the ice as world champions and extending
to them our best wishes for much continued success in their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we honor and recognize Jack Hughes for his
resiliency in returning to the ice after suffering a major injury to score the winning goal in
overtime of the gold medal match, thus earning the eternal gratitude of a nation.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
